Subject: Re: [VB] upright motor and 78 tranny !

The buggy guys do it all the time, but the input shaft is a bit longer and
will stick into the gland nut a bit too far.  You can cut 3/8" or so off.
That tranny has some pretty tall gears for a stock 1600.

